1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. Bd3 {The Schlechter Variation, the bad cousin of 3. Nc3 and 
3. Nd2 aiming to defend the e4-pawn. Unlike his cousins he cannot defend himself 
from attack leading to time loss and quick equality for Black.} dxe4 4. Bxe4 Nf6 
{[%cal Gf6e4][%csl Re4]} 5. Bf3 {The major branches of the line start here on 
move five.} (5. Bd3 c5 6. dxc5 Bxc5) (5. Bg5 c5 6. c3 cxd4 7. cxd4 Qa5+) c5 
{[%cal Gd8d1][%csl Rd4]} 6. Ne2 Nc6 7. Be3 cxd4 8. Nxd4 Ne5 {[%csl Rf3]} 9. Nc3 
Bb4 10. Ndb5 Bd7 11. Nd6+ {This is too greedy.} (11. a3 Bxc3+ 12. Nxc3 Bc6) Ke7 
{Black's king is safe and White has to be careful not to strand the knight.} 12. 
Nxb7 ({If} 12. Ne4 {then} 12... Bc6) Qc8 {[%csl Rb7]} 13. a3 Nxf3+ 14. Qxf3 
Bxc3+ 15. bxc3 Qxc3+ $19 {[%cal Bd7b5,Gb5f1,Gc3e1,Gc3a1][%csl Re1,Ra1] Baum, 
Jonasz - Kanmazalp, O., 0-1, Graz Open A 2018.} *

