1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. c4 {The Steiner Variation. This is a typically odd try to 
take an edge by giving up a center pawn. This opening attempt for White falls 
flat.} dxe4 4. Nc3 Nf6 {[%cal Gf6e4][%csl Ge4]} 5. Bg5 (5. f3 c5 6. d5 exd5 7. 
cxd5 Bd6) h6 (5... Be7 {would be a fine alternative.}) 6. Bxf6 Qxf6 {The point 
is that White has practical trouble recapturing on e4.} 7. Nxe4 $6 Bb4+ 8. Nc3 
c5 {[%cal Gf6c3,Gb4c3,Gc5d4][%csl Rd4,Rc3]} 9. Nge2 O-O 10. a3 Bxc3+ 11. bxc3 
Rd8 $19 {[%cal Gc5d4,Gf6d4,Gd8d4,Bb8c6][%csl Rd4] White can't develop without 
the center collapsing.} *

