1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. Be3 {The Alapin, another variation where White willingly 
gives up a center pawn.} dxe4 4. f3 {This is a serious attempt at Morra-type 
gambit play where White is attempting to sacrifice a pawn to accelerate 
development. We simply choose not to allow this.} Nf6 {[%cal Gf6e4]} 5. Nc3 
{[%cal Gc3e4]} (5. Nd2 Nd5) Bb4 {[%cal Gb4e1][%csl Rc3]} 6. Bg5 h6 7. Bh4 (7. 
Bxf6 Qxf6 8. fxe4 Qh4+) Nc6 {[%cal Bf3e4,Bg7g5]} 8. Nge2 O-O 9. fxe4 g5 {[%cal 
Bf6e4] White doesn't hold onto the e4-pawn for long.} 10. Bg3 Nxe4 $17 *

